<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 2:36PM EDT  by NWS Wilmington</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF SOUTHERN KENTON,
SOUTHERN BOONE, NORTHERN GRANT, WEST CENTRAL PENDLETON AND EASTERN
GALLATIN COUNTIES THROUGH 300 PM EDT...
At 235 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Crittenden,
moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to outdoor
objects.
Locations impacted include...
Independence, Walton, Crittenden, Munk, Atwood, Ryle, Bank Lick,
Morning View, Bracht, Gardnersville, Fiskburg, Beaverlick, Sherman,
Verona, Piner and Elliston.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.
To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.</instruction>
